    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I noticed that the `change_version.sh` script does the replacing below:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/46a06069c605842111d68b85b3e9aeea1974e202/scripts/change_version.sh#L34\r\n\r\nthe `VERSION_CRATE` variable points `lighthouse_version/src/lib.rs`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/46a06069c605842111d68b85b3e9aeea1974e202/scripts/change_version.sh#L17\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nTherefore we don't need to use `env!(\"CARGO_PKG_VERSION\")`, just hard code the version number. ðŸ’¡ \r\n\r\n```diff\r\npub const VERSION: &str = git_version!(\r\n    args = [\r\n        \"--always\",\r\n        \"--dirty=+\",\r\n        \"--abbrev=7\",\r\n        // NOTE: using --match instead of --exclude for compatibility with old Git\r\n        \"--match=thiswillnevermatchlol\"\r\n    ],\r\n    prefix = \"Lighthouse/v2.2.1-\",\r\n-   fallback = \"unknown\"\r\n+   fallback = \"Lighthouse/v2.2.1\" // Note: unlike `prefix`, the trailing hyphen was striped.\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
